  "prompt": "What is the syllabus of amcat?",
  "response": "The **AMCAT (Aspiring Minds Computer Adaptive Test)** is an employability test widely used for evaluating the skills of graduates across different domains. The syllabus for AMCAT is divided into **compulsory modules** (tested for all candidates) and **optional modules** (based on the candidate's field of study or career choice). Here's a detailed breakdown of the syllabus:\n\n---\n\n### **Compulsory Modules**\nThese are mandatory for all candidates:\n1. **English Communication**  \n   - Vocabulary (synonyms, antonyms, word meanings)  \n   - Grammar (error spotting, sentence correction)  \n   - Reading Comprehension  \n   - Sentence Formation and Ordering\n\n2. **Quantitative Ability**  \n   - Basic Arithmetic (percentages, ratios, averages)  \n   - Algebra  \n   - Geometry  \n   - Number Systems  \n   - Probability and Permutation-Combination  \n   - Data Interpretation (tables, charts, graphs)\n\n3. **Logical Ability**  \n   - Logical Reasoning (deductive/inductive reasoning)  \n   - Data Sufficiency  \n   - Seating Arrangement  \n   - Coding-Decoding  \n   - Puzzles  \n   - Series and Patterns\n\n---\n\n### **Optional Modules**\nThese are chosen based on the candidate\u2019s field of study or career aspirations. Common optional modules include:\n\n#### **Core Engineering Modules**\n1. **Computer Science/IT**  \n   - Programming (C, C++, Java, Python)  \n   - Data Structures and Algorithms  \n   - DBMS (Database Management Systems)  \n   - Operating Systems  \n   - Networking  \n   - Software Engineering  \n\n2. **Electrical Engineering**  \n   - Circuit Theory  \n   - Control Systems  \n   - Electrical Machines  \n   - Power Systems  \n   - Signals and Systems  \n\n3. **Mechanical Engineering**  \n   - Thermodynamics  \n   - Fluid Mechanics  \n   - Manufacturing Processes  \n   - Strength of Materials  \n   - Machine Design  \n\n4. **Electronics Engineering**  \n   - Electronic Devices and Circuits  \n   - Digital Electronics  \n   - Microprocessors  \n   - Communication Systems  \n\n#### **Non-Engineering Modules**\n1. **Finance**  \n   - Accounting Basics  \n   - Financial Management  \n   - Stock Valuation  \n   - Risk Analysis  \n\n2. **Marketing**  \n   - Marketing Basics  \n   - Consumer Behavior  \n   - Market Research  \n   - Brand Management  \n\n3. **Human Resources**  \n   - Organizational Behavior  \n   - Recruitment and Selection  \n   - Training and Development  \n   - Employee Relations  \n\n4. **Operations**  \n   - Supply Chain Management  \n   - Inventory Management  \n   - Quality Control  \n   - Production Planning  \n\n5. **Customer Service**  \n   - Communication Skills  \n   - Conflict Resolution  \n   - Customer Relationship Management (CRM)  \n\n---\n\n### **Other Modules**\n1. **Automata** (for programming roles)  \n   - Hands-on coding questions (e.g., debugging, writing code)  \n\n2. **Personality Assessment**  \n   - Behavioral traits, strengths, and areas for improvement (not scored but used for job fitment).  \n\n---\n\n### **Scoring and Sections**\n- The number of questions and duration vary for each module.  \n- Scores are provided for each module, and a **percentile score** is calculated.  \n- Employers use these scores to assess a candidate\u2019s suitability for specific roles.\n\n**Note**: The exact syllabus may vary slightly depending on the company\u2019s requirements or the version of the AMCAT being administered. It is recommended to check the official **AMCAT website** or the test registration portal for the most accurate and updated syllabus.\n\nLet me know if you need further details!",
